First they came for JNU & Jamia students, and I did not speak out - 
because I was told that they were Urban Naxals 
Then they came for free-thinkers, teachers & the syllabus, and i did not speak out - 
because the news said that this was the decolonisation process 
Then they came for our jobs, and I did not speak out - 
because Supreme Leader told me to open a Pakoda stall instead
Then they came for my entrance exams - 
and there was no one left to speak for my future.

comments.text:
Hello Akash sir, 
I am Armaan Soni from Punjab and I am writing this mail to bring your attention to an issue about the CET examination which is a new examination this year for BMS/BCA and other few courses for the students who just gave 12th boards. This examination took place on 29th May and its portal for application was open for more than 1 month and was reopened 2 times for students to apply and around 57,000 students registered for the examination. The exam took place and its results were to be announced on 17th June but for some reason the results were not out and no clarification was given by the CET cell so we students thought that there might be a little delay in the examination result and waited for 2,3 days but now CET cell is telling us that they are re-conducting the examinations because many students are sending them mails that they did not know about the examination and and the students who did not gave the examination earlier can now give examination while they have back up options applied for because they did not give the exam earlier, but the students who did not apply for the back up options because they had good CET exam score are now suffering to get into any college as this whole process is delayed for around two months by the CET cell and nobody is talking about it because it is not a famous exam.
That's why I wanted to request you to bring a little light to this situation because it is very hard for the students who gave the examination and who are getting good marks(According to the answer key) please stand from our side because all the students who gave the examination according to the earlier schedule now suffering with anxiety and depression of not getting into any college at least suggest CET cell that they should first allot the seats to the students who earlier gave the examination and rest of the seats should be given to the students who miss the examination, but please bring a little light to the situation because it is very hard to fight when no one is standing with you, and no one is hearing you.
Thankyou I will wait for a positive response like I wait to get a reply from CET cell.
